      "content": "To guarantee a perfect 1.0 parity score, you must precisely calculate the required number of duplicates for each minority class based on the size of the largest class. Formulaically, for any minority class $C_i$, you must oversample it by a factor of $\\lceil \\text{Size}(\\text{Majority Class}) / \\text{Size}(C_i) \\rceil$. This targeted multiplication ensures every class count becomes identical, mathematically enforcing the desired 50/50 split standard for your report.",
